    ) VALUES (1504531, 'Anisindione', 'Etravirine', 'Moderate', 'Coadministration with etravirine may increase the plasma concentrations of warfarin. The proposed mechanism is etravirine inhibition of CYP450 2C19 and 2C9, the isoenzymes responsible for the metabolic clearance of the R(+) and S(-) enantiomers of warfarin, respectively.', NULL, 'Given the potential for interaction and the high degree of interpatient variability with respect to warfarin metabolism, patients should be closely monitored during concomitant therapy with etravirine.', NULL, 'Given the potential for interaction and the high degree of interpatient variability with respect to warfarin metabolism, patients should be closely monitored during concomitant therapy with etravirine. The INR should be checked frequently and warfarin dosage adjusted accordingly, particularly following initiation or discontinuation of etravirine in patients who are stabilized on their warfarin regimen. The same precaution may be applicable during therapy with other oral anticoagulants, although clinical and pharmacokinetic data are lacking. Patients should be advised to promptly report any signs of bleeding to their physician, including pain, swelling, headache, dizziness, weakness, prolonged bleeding from cuts, increased menstrual flow, vaginal bleeding, nosebleeds, bleeding of gums from brushing, unusual bleeding or bruising, red or brown urine, or red or black stools.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', 1767317477);
